<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: after-white-space;"><p =
dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Good afternoon David and =
Chris,</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for =
your follow-up email, David, and for clarifying the misunderstanding =
from our call. I appreciate your flexibility, and since you=E2=80=99re =
busy on Tuesday, Wednesday at 2:00 PM works for me=E2=80=94please =
confirm if that suits.</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">Before we proceed, I want to reiterate two key priorities to =
ensure a safe and effective process:</p><ul =
dir=3D"auto"><li><strong>Health &amp; Safety (H&amp;S) Risk =
Mitigation</strong>: No work should start until H&amp;S risks are =
identified and addressed by independent experts, given the master =
electrician=E2=80=99s finding that the property is uninhabitable due to =
electrical hazards.</li><li><strong>Assessment-Focused Work</strong>: =
Initial tasks should enable damage assessment (e.g., securing the site, =
removing debris for inspection) rather than repairs (e.g., cleaning =
curtains or upholstery), allowing me to exercise my right to an =
independent assessment and for both parties to agree on a remediation =
plan.</li></ul><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">I=E2=80=99=
ve been told by firefighters that there was substantial fire damage and =
significant smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially thought to =
originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which penetrated the =
house structure. Yet, the roof, the gas unit beneath it, and overall =
structural integrity remain uninspected.This, alongside asbestos and =
moisture concerns, raises serious safety issues.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">I=E2=80=99m particularly worried about =
the asbestos plan. The scope mentions removing less than 10m=C2=B2, but =
the deck=E2=80=99s fire-damaged section connects to the main area, =
suggesting potential wider involvement. I raised this with Chris, =
requesting a full inspection, and I=E2=80=99d like this addressed before =
any removal begins.</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">Could we please align on this H&amp;S-first, assessment-only =
approach? I=E2=80=99d prefer to defer repair-focused cleaning until =
after experts assess the damage and we agree on a plan. This seems fair =
to ensure safety and accuracy=E2=80=94do you agree? I=E2=80=99m happy to =
discuss this onsite at 2:00 PM Wednesday if confirmed.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks so much for your =
understanding=E2=80=94I look forward to your response.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Kind regards,<br>
Raffaella del Prete</p><div class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" =
